WEBVTT

00:02.635 --> 00:03.969
<i>- ♪ Crashing through</i>
<i>the crowded halls ♪</i>

00:04.037 --> 00:05.705
<i>♪ Dodging girls</i>
<i>like Ping-Pong balls ♪</i>

00:05.772 --> 00:07.240
<i>♪ Just to reach the bathroom</i>
<i>on time ♪</i>

00:07.307 --> 00:08.641
<i>♪ Leaping over laundry piles ♪</i>

00:08.708 --> 00:10.543
<i>♪ Diapers you can smell</i>
<i>for miles ♪</i>

00:10.610 --> 00:13.980
<i>♪ Guy's got to do</i>
<i>what he can to survive ♪</i>

00:14.047 --> 00:15.048
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:15.115 --> 00:16.483
<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>

00:16.549 --> 00:17.650
<i>- ♪ Duck, dodge, push,</i>
<i>and shove ♪</i>

00:17.717 --> 00:19.386
<i>♪ Is how we show our love ♪</i>

00:19.452 --> 00:21.421
<i>- ♪ In the Loud house,</i>
<i>in the Loud house ♪</i>

00:21.488 --> 00:22.922
<i>- ♪ One boy and ten girls ♪</i>

00:22.989 --> 00:24.924
<i>♪ Wouldn't trade it</i>
<i>for the world ♪</i>

00:24.991 --> 00:28.061
<i>- ♪ Loud Loud Loud ♪</i>

00:28.128 --> 00:29.396
{\an8}<i>♪ Loud house ♪</i>

00:29.462 --> 00:30.597
{\an8}- Poo-poo.

00:34.701 --> 00:37.637
<i>[rock music]</i>

00:37.704 --> 00:42.642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:42.709 --> 00:45.378
[crickets chirping]

00:45.445 --> 00:48.381
- [snoring]

00:50.083 --> 00:51.418
[static]
Ah!

00:51.484 --> 00:53.887
<i>- Slumberjack, come in.</i>
<i>It's Night Owl.</i>

00:53.953 --> 00:55.522
<i>Slumberjack, do you read me?</i>

00:55.588 --> 00:56.556
{\an3}- Clyde?

00:56.623 --> 00:57.757
- Sorry about the late hour,

00:57.824 --> 01:00.160
but I have the best news ever.

01:00.226 --> 01:02.862
{\an3}- Lori found the book of poems
you wrote about her

01:02.929 --> 01:04.631
{\an3}and realized
she's in love with you?

01:04.697 --> 01:06.232
- Okay, second-best news ever.

01:06.299 --> 01:08.201
My dads are having another baby.
- [gasps]

01:08.268 --> 01:10.670
- I'm going to be a big brother.
- Clyde, that's amazing.

01:10.737 --> 01:13.540
Did they just tell you?
- Well, not exactly.

01:13.606 --> 01:16.543
{\an1}But I've been noticing
clues for a while.

01:16.609 --> 01:18.845
[whistling]

01:18.912 --> 01:20.580
Baby clothes?

01:20.647 --> 01:22.949
{\an8}<i>[jazzy bass music]</i>

01:23.016 --> 01:24.684
{\an8}Baby bottles?

01:24.751 --> 01:26.419
{\an8}Come on, Cleopawtra.

01:26.486 --> 01:30.256
{\an7}- There, can't be too safe
with a little one on the loose.

01:30.323 --> 01:32.792
{\an9}- [gasps] That reminds me,
we need to secure loose cables,

01:32.859 --> 01:35.895
{\an9}and cover the outlets, and
lock up the cleaning supplies.

01:35.962 --> 01:37.597
{\an1}- So it was pretty clear
what was going on,

01:37.664 --> 01:40.533
{\an1}but I wasn't positive
until about five minutes ago.

01:40.600 --> 01:43.169
- Well, Howie,
I think our home is ready,

01:43.236 --> 01:44.671
but what about our hearts?

01:44.737 --> 01:45.939
Do we really have room

01:46.005 --> 01:48.408
for another little
bundle of joy?

01:48.475 --> 01:50.410
- Of course we do, Harebear.
[gasps]

01:50.477 --> 01:52.512
I cannot wait
to surprise Clyde.

01:55.215 --> 01:57.283
{\an1}- Being a big brother
is the most important job

01:57.350 --> 02:00.019
{\an1}I'll ever have, apart
from being Lori's soul mate.

02:00.086 --> 02:01.454
{\an1}I need to make sure
I'm ready for it.

02:01.521 --> 02:03.223
{\an3}- You woke up
the right guy, Clyde.

02:03.289 --> 02:06.059
{\an3}I've got the big brother thing
down to a science.

02:06.125 --> 02:07.861
{\an3}Why don't you spend a day
shadowing me

02:07.927 --> 02:09.362
so you can learn firsthand?

02:09.429 --> 02:10.964
- Sweet! I'm on my way!

02:11.030 --> 02:13.099
{\an3}- Love that enthusiasm,
Night Owl,

02:13.166 --> 02:14.100
but it's 1:00 a.m.

02:14.167 --> 02:15.101
- [laughs] Right.

02:15.168 --> 02:16.436
{\an1}See you at 9:00,
Slumberjack.

02:16.503 --> 02:18.471
{\an3}- Sleep well,
Night Owl.

02:18.538 --> 02:20.273
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

02:20.340 --> 02:23.543
{\an3}Okay, Clyde,
allow me to introduce...

02:23.610 --> 02:26.546
{\an3}Lincoln Loud's three Cs
of big brothering:

02:26.613 --> 02:28.047
confidence, caring,

02:28.114 --> 02:29.849
and when all else fails,

02:29.916 --> 02:32.218
{\an3}cookies!

02:32.285 --> 02:34.587
{\an1}- Snickerdoodles.
My favorite!

02:34.654 --> 02:37.090
{\an3}- Ah, ah, ah.
Those aren't for us.

02:37.156 --> 02:38.591
Now, time to start my rounds

02:38.658 --> 02:41.861
{\an3}so you can observe
the three Cs in action.

02:41.928 --> 02:43.363
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:43.429 --> 02:45.131
- [wailing]
- Hear that?

02:45.198 --> 02:47.467
First big brother cue
of the day.

02:47.534 --> 02:50.570
- [wailing]
- First up, confidence.

02:50.637 --> 02:54.207
{\an3}Don't worry, Lily.
Your big brother's here to help.

02:54.274 --> 02:56.075
{\an3}Let's get a look
at that thumb of yours.

02:56.142 --> 02:57.343
- [whimpering]

02:57.410 --> 02:59.779
{\an3}- Just what I thought,
a boo-boo.

02:59.846 --> 03:01.581
This calls for caring.

03:01.648 --> 03:04.417
{\an3}Aw, I'm sorry you got
such a bad ouchie,

03:04.484 --> 03:07.620
but we can make it better.

03:07.687 --> 03:10.223
{\an1}- [cooing]

03:10.290 --> 03:12.425
{\an9}- Wow, you didn't even
need a cookie.

03:12.492 --> 03:14.360
{\an7}- Cookie?

03:14.427 --> 03:16.462
{\an8}- Sometimes
it's safer to spell.

03:16.529 --> 03:18.398
{\an3}- Lana!

03:18.464 --> 03:21.301
{\an3}Stop it!
- Make me!

03:21.367 --> 03:22.936
- Sounds like a twin fight.

03:23.002 --> 03:24.971
This should be very educational.

03:25.038 --> 03:27.540
[grunting and smacking]

03:27.607 --> 03:29.943
{\an1}All right, Clyde.
What do you think we need here?

03:30.009 --> 03:31.911
- Um, confidence?

03:31.978 --> 03:33.613
[smacking]

03:33.680 --> 03:36.082
- What seems to be
the problem?

03:36.149 --> 03:37.584
{\an8}- Lana's supposed to be guarding

03:37.650 --> 03:39.652
{\an8}my princess tower,
not attacking it!

03:39.719 --> 03:42.655
{\an8}- Now, Lana--
- Ah, guarding is boring!

03:42.722 --> 03:44.991
Attacking is cool.

03:45.058 --> 03:47.260
[grunting]

03:47.327 --> 03:48.962
- Clyde, any guesses?

03:49.028 --> 03:51.598
- Um, caring?

03:51.664 --> 03:55.034
- I think I know a compromise
that will make you both happy.

03:55.101 --> 03:57.670
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

03:57.737 --> 04:00.506
{\an1}The evil troll's
attacking your tower.

04:00.573 --> 04:03.509
Rawr!
both: Get him!

04:03.576 --> 04:05.345
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:05.411 --> 04:06.713
- Nice, and once again,

04:06.779 --> 04:09.282
{\an1}you didn't need
the C-O-O-K-I-E-S.

04:09.349 --> 04:11.317
{\an3}both: The troll's
got cookies!

04:11.384 --> 04:12.885
{\an8}[all grunting]
- I saw them!

04:12.952 --> 04:14.420
{\an8}- Another tip...
[grunting]

04:14.487 --> 04:17.089
{\an8}Six-year-olds can spell.
[grunting]

04:17.156 --> 04:18.458
{\an8}- I need--
- Cookies!

04:18.524 --> 04:21.226
{\an3}- Elder brother,
I require your assistance.

04:21.293 --> 04:22.962
{\an1}- What can I
help you with, Lisa?

04:23.029 --> 04:25.498
Lab explosion?
Nuclear crisis?

04:25.565 --> 04:27.834
{\an3}- No, I have a hankering
for a PB&amp;J.

04:27.900 --> 04:29.836
- Coming right up.

04:29.902 --> 04:31.137
{\an8}- I can isolate uranium,

04:31.204 --> 04:33.439
{\an7}but they won't let me
use a butter knife.

04:33.506 --> 04:36.509
{\an7}Also, I like the way Lincoln
makes my sandwiches.

04:36.576 --> 04:39.679
{\an7}- Here you go, easy
on the jelly, crusts cut off,

04:39.746 --> 04:43.216
{\an1}and sliced into four right
triangles for optimum mouth fit.

04:43.282 --> 04:45.251
- Thank you.
Technically, they're isosceles,

04:45.318 --> 04:48.254
but I'm not gonna bite
the hand that feeds me.

04:48.321 --> 04:49.622
- Ah!
- Hey, Lincoln.

04:49.689 --> 04:51.357
{\an1}Could you help me
with a poem for school?

04:51.424 --> 04:53.726
I need a rhyme for "tomb."

04:53.793 --> 04:57.230
- Hmm. "Gloom"? "Doom"?
"Powder room"?

04:57.296 --> 04:59.132
{\an1}- I knew
I could depend on you.

04:59.198 --> 05:03.469
{\an1}[sniffs]
Do I smell snickerdoodles?

05:03.536 --> 05:06.105
{\an3}- It's a real pleasure
to watch a master at work.

05:06.172 --> 05:08.207
{\an1}- Eh, I've had
a lot of practice.

05:08.274 --> 05:10.376
{\an1}- Give it!
- No! You give it!

05:10.443 --> 05:12.245
- You ready to get
some practice too?

05:12.311 --> 05:13.813
{\an3}- Heck yes!

05:13.880 --> 05:16.249
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

05:16.315 --> 05:17.483
[grunting and smacking]

05:17.550 --> 05:19.452
Okay, Clyde. Confidence.

05:19.519 --> 05:22.288
{\an7}Um, hey, guys,
do you think you could just--

05:22.355 --> 05:23.489
{\an8}[grunting and smacking]

05:23.556 --> 05:26.693
{\an8}[crunch]
Ah! That was my foot!

05:26.759 --> 05:27.727
{\an8}[grunting and smacking]

05:27.794 --> 05:29.862
{\an8}What seems to be
the problem here?

05:29.929 --> 05:31.230
{\an8}- You? Where's Lincoln?

05:31.297 --> 05:32.865
{\an8}- I'm temporarily
filling in for him

05:32.932 --> 05:35.702
{\an7}and would be happy to help you
settle your differences.

05:35.768 --> 05:37.670
{\an8}- Lisa stole my best rat,
Bitey!

05:37.737 --> 05:41.941
{\an9}- Who's Bitey?
This is Subject 57A.

05:42.008 --> 05:43.309
{\an7}- Ah!

05:43.376 --> 05:45.778
{\an7}Uh, well, you both
seem attached to it,

05:45.845 --> 05:47.280
{\an8}and I want to be fair--

05:47.346 --> 05:48.848
Ah!
- Hey, Clyde, I need advice.

05:48.915 --> 05:50.817
How do you know
you've met your soul mate?

05:50.883 --> 05:51.951
- Oh, uh, wow.

05:52.018 --> 05:53.186
That's some serious stuff.

05:53.252 --> 05:54.721
How much time do you have?

05:54.787 --> 05:56.556
- Lincoln!

05:56.622 --> 06:00.293
Clyde! Help me choreograph
my ribbon dance!

06:00.359 --> 06:01.627
- Hold on a sec, Lucy.

06:01.694 --> 06:03.996
Did Lincoln even go
over ribbon dancing?

06:04.063 --> 06:06.766
- [whimpers] Boo-boo.

06:06.833 --> 06:10.236
{\an1}- Just another minute, Lucy.
Hang on, Lola.

06:10.303 --> 06:11.571
{\an1}Whoops.

06:11.637 --> 06:13.473
{\an8}- [wailing]
- No, no, no, no, no. Wait.

06:13.539 --> 06:16.075
{\an8}It's all okay. Shh. Shh.

06:16.142 --> 06:17.944
{\an8}Ah!
- [wailing]

06:18.010 --> 06:20.947
[all shouting at once]

06:23.149 --> 06:24.917
- [struggling]

06:24.984 --> 06:27.453
Just take the cookies!

06:27.520 --> 06:28.855
[all gasping]

06:28.921 --> 06:30.523
- [squeaks]

06:30.590 --> 06:32.058
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

06:32.125 --> 06:34.827
- Clyde! What happened?

06:34.894 --> 06:36.763
{\an8}- L-L-L-L-Lori?

06:36.829 --> 06:38.297
{\an8}[moans]

06:38.364 --> 06:39.932
{\an9}- Whatever.

06:41.467 --> 06:43.369
<i>[suspenseful chimes]</i>

06:43.436 --> 06:45.238
- Clyde. Talk to me, buddy.

06:45.304 --> 06:46.639
What happened back there?

06:46.706 --> 06:49.375
{\an1}- [sighs]
I failed at the three Cs.

06:49.442 --> 06:50.843
{\an3}- What?
How is that possible?

06:50.910 --> 06:52.612
{\an3}You're the most caring
person I know.

06:52.678 --> 06:54.480
And you make great cookies.

06:54.547 --> 06:56.215
- It's the confidence
I'm struggling with.

06:56.282 --> 06:57.617
What if I give bad crush advice,

06:57.683 --> 06:59.685
{\an1}and my future sibling
gets their heart broken?

06:59.752 --> 07:01.320
{\an8}Or what if I can't choreograph
a ribbon dance,

07:01.387 --> 07:02.655
{\an8}and they drop out of school

07:02.722 --> 07:04.624
{\an8}and start holding up
convenience stores?

07:04.690 --> 07:06.526
{\an8}I'm going to be
a terrible big brother!

07:06.592 --> 07:07.994
- Clyde, you're spiraling!

07:08.060 --> 07:09.061
You can do this.

07:09.128 --> 07:10.463
{\an1}Just get out there
and try again.

07:10.530 --> 07:12.665
- I can't, Lincoln!

07:12.732 --> 07:14.834
{\an3}I don't have
the confidence you do,

07:14.901 --> 07:16.903
and I never will.

07:16.969 --> 07:18.337
- It's okay, buddy.

07:18.404 --> 07:19.672
How about we just forget
the whole

07:19.739 --> 07:22.074
training thing
and play some video games?

07:22.141 --> 07:23.509
- That sounds great.

07:23.576 --> 07:26.045
{\an3}- I'll just go
grab us some snacks.

07:28.214 --> 07:30.082
- Lincoln?
- Ah! Sister!

07:30.149 --> 07:31.450
I mean, hi, Lisa.

07:31.517 --> 07:34.220
{\an9}- I require assistance
securing my shoestrings.

07:34.287 --> 07:36.389
{\an8}- Aren't you a certified genius?

07:36.455 --> 07:38.858
{\an9}- Yes, which is why
there is no room

07:38.925 --> 07:41.661
{\an9}in my brain
for such trivialities.

07:43.462 --> 07:44.597
Thanks, Clyde.

07:44.664 --> 07:46.833
You're a lifesaver.

07:46.899 --> 07:48.401
- Where's Lincoln?
- Ah!

07:48.467 --> 07:50.436
{\an3}I mean, you might want
to try the kitchen.

07:50.503 --> 07:54.640
{\an1}- What's a long walk.
I need a rhyme for "Lori."

07:54.707 --> 07:56.676
{\an3}- Really?
Well, I've got about a hundred.

07:56.742 --> 07:59.111
{\an3}"Story," "glory,"
"Montessori"...

07:59.178 --> 08:00.947
And "inventory."

08:01.013 --> 08:02.815
Now, those are just
the ones in English.

08:02.882 --> 08:05.585
{\an3}- Thanks, Clyde.
You're a lifesaver.

08:05.651 --> 08:07.253
[horn beeps, tires squeal]
- Where's Lincoln?

08:07.320 --> 08:09.789
{\an3}I need him to show me
how to buckle my seat belt.

08:09.856 --> 08:11.524
{\an7}- Oh.
Well, that's simple enough.

08:11.591 --> 08:12.892
{\an8}Why don't I show you?

08:12.959 --> 08:14.961
Just insert the metal fitting
into the buckle

08:15.027 --> 08:16.963
and pull tightly
across your waist.

08:17.029 --> 08:19.732
To release, simply press
the center button.

08:19.799 --> 08:21.868
[seat belt clicks]
- Oh!

08:21.934 --> 08:25.037
I never could have
figured that out.

08:26.305 --> 08:28.474
You're a lifesaver, Clydey.

08:28.541 --> 08:30.042
[tires squealing]

08:32.410 --> 08:35.313
{\an8}- You--you want me
to read to you?

08:35.381 --> 08:37.783
{\an3}Um...

08:37.850 --> 08:40.886
"And Z is for 'zucchini.'
The end."

08:40.953 --> 08:42.889
- [giggling]

08:44.222 --> 08:45.725
- Hey, Lincoln! Guess what!

08:45.791 --> 08:48.361
{\an3}I think I have
the missing C now.

08:48.427 --> 08:50.196
Lincoln?
- Okay.

08:50.263 --> 08:51.764
I did the damsel
in distress act.

08:51.831 --> 08:53.833
Now where's my 5 bucks?

08:53.900 --> 08:55.668
- Yeah, pay up.

08:55.735 --> 08:57.103
{\an3}- I should be
doubly compensated

08:57.169 --> 08:59.372
{\an3}for having to act
like such an ignoramus.

08:59.438 --> 09:01.974
- You staged that whole thing?

09:02.041 --> 09:03.342
{\an1}- Clyde!
I can explain.

09:03.409 --> 09:05.945
{\an1}I was just trying
to boost your confidence.

09:08.514 --> 09:10.516
- I think I should go.

09:12.151 --> 09:15.288
- Clyde, wait!

09:15.354 --> 09:16.756
- [cooing]

09:17.924 --> 09:19.358
- Clyde! Help!

09:19.425 --> 09:21.694
I can't get down!

09:21.761 --> 09:23.029
- You can save the act, Lana.

09:23.095 --> 09:25.331
{\an1}I know Lincoln's
paying you to do this.

09:25.398 --> 09:26.565
- What are you talking about?

09:26.632 --> 09:28.034
Bitey and I are really stuck,

09:28.100 --> 09:31.037
{\an3}and I think
he's afraid of heights.

09:31.103 --> 09:33.372
And maybe I am too.

09:33.439 --> 09:35.574
{\an7}- It's okay, Lana.
Don't be scared.

09:35.641 --> 09:38.144
{\an8}I'll rescue you!

09:38.210 --> 09:40.780
{\an8}You guys doing okay?

09:40.846 --> 09:42.114
{\an8}I know what it's like.

09:42.181 --> 09:43.983
{\an8}One time, I got stuck
on a diving board.

09:44.050 --> 09:46.218
{\an8}And a step stool.

09:46.285 --> 09:48.154
{\an7}- Yay!

09:48.220 --> 09:49.755
{\an8}- Here. You've earned it.

09:49.822 --> 09:52.825
{\an7}- I don't know what I would have
done without you, Clyde.

09:54.760 --> 09:56.829
{\an8}Oh, you're a real lifesaver!

09:56.896 --> 09:58.798
{\an3}- Clyde.
I thought you left.

09:58.864 --> 10:01.567
Look, I owe you an apology--
- It's okay, Lincoln.

10:01.634 --> 10:04.303
{\an1}I finally got my confidence,
for real this time.

10:04.370 --> 10:07.139
{\an1}I got to go tell my dads
I'm ready to be a big brother.

10:07.206 --> 10:09.809
- Good luck, buddy.
You're gonna do great.

10:09.875 --> 10:12.044
- Lisa! Move your big butt!

10:12.111 --> 10:16.115
{\an3}- Move your own
oversized posterior!

10:16.182 --> 10:19.785
- Ah, a big brother's work
is never done.

10:19.852 --> 10:22.254
- Clyde, honey, we have
something to tell you.

10:22.321 --> 10:24.557
{\an3}- I already know what it is.
We're having a baby,

10:24.623 --> 10:26.926
{\an3}and I'm gonna be a big brother,
and it's gonna be great,

10:26.993 --> 10:28.594
{\an3}'cause Lincoln taught me
the three Cs,

10:28.661 --> 10:30.262
{\an3}and I can't wait to start
baking cookies and--

10:30.329 --> 10:33.599
- Clyde, you're spiraling.
- And did you say "baby"?

10:33.666 --> 10:35.801
{\an3}- Yeah, I saw the bottles
and the clothes,

10:35.868 --> 10:38.604
and I heard you guys talking.

10:38.671 --> 10:41.073
{\an1}- I'm afraid there's been
a bit of a mix-up.

10:41.140 --> 10:43.976
{\an1}Your dad and I haven't been
preparing for a baby.

10:45.478 --> 10:47.880
- We've been preparing for...

10:47.947 --> 10:49.115
a kitten!

10:49.181 --> 10:52.985
{\an1}Meet Cleopawtra's sister,
Ne-purr-titi!

10:53.052 --> 10:55.621
{\an1}We finally got to bring her home
from the shelter today!

10:55.688 --> 10:57.690
- Wow, she's perfect!

10:57.757 --> 11:00.459
And just so you guys know,
if you ever do decide

11:00.526 --> 11:01.927
to have another human child,

11:01.994 --> 11:03.796
I'm totally ready for it.

11:05.965 --> 11:07.099
- We'll be back in an hour.

11:07.166 --> 11:09.468
{\an1}You okay keeping an eye
on the kitties?

11:09.535 --> 11:10.970
- I've got the three Cs:

11:11.037 --> 11:13.973
caring, confidence,
and cat treats.

11:14.040 --> 11:15.741
{\an8}[cats yowling]

11:15.808 --> 11:17.943
{\an8}Whoops, guess I should have
spelled that.

11:22.314 --> 11:25.251
<i>[rock music]</i>

11:25.317 --> 11:30.456
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:33.426 --> 11:36.295
- [whistling]

11:38.964 --> 11:41.100
{\an3}- Sorry, bro.
Kitchen's off-limits.

11:41.167 --> 11:42.468
Lori's in there cooling off.

11:42.535 --> 11:44.703
{\an3}She and Leni had
a major throwdown.

11:44.770 --> 11:47.339
{\an1}- Yeah, sad story,
but I'm hungry.

11:47.406 --> 11:48.841
- Fear not, male sibling.

11:48.908 --> 11:51.210
{\an1}You should be able
to satiate your appetite

11:51.277 --> 11:53.145
{\an1}by foraging under
the couch cushions.

11:53.212 --> 11:54.380
See what I scored?

11:54.447 --> 11:58.017
- Ooh, an everything bagel.

11:58.084 --> 12:00.152
{\an8}- Mm, correction:
a plain bagel...

12:00.219 --> 12:02.788
{\an7}with lint, dog hair, and--
[gasps]

12:02.855 --> 12:05.524
{\an8}gadzooks, is that a booger?

12:07.359 --> 12:10.196
{\an3}- Ah, do not eat
the "couch bagel."

12:10.262 --> 12:11.997
- Sorry, bathroom's off-limits.

12:12.064 --> 12:13.799
{\an1}Leni's in there cooling off
from the fight.

12:13.866 --> 12:16.669
Here. Use this.
- A bucket? [gulps]

12:16.735 --> 12:19.371
- Don't knock it
till you try it.

12:23.442 --> 12:26.112
[grunting and smacking]

12:26.178 --> 12:28.314
- Sorry, TV's off-limits.

12:28.380 --> 12:30.316
- Oh, come on! Why?

12:30.382 --> 12:31.851
- Lori and Leni are on edge.

12:31.917 --> 12:34.887
{\an1}You watching a monster truck
rally is not going to help them.

12:34.954 --> 12:38.424
- This is ridiculous--what are
they even fighting about?

12:38.491 --> 12:40.025
[all talking at once]

12:40.092 --> 12:41.360
- Guys, guys, guys.

12:41.427 --> 12:42.828
Check out this dress
I found at the mall.

12:42.895 --> 12:46.232
It's literally one-of-a-kind.
Yay!

12:46.298 --> 12:47.600
all: Ooh!

12:47.666 --> 12:49.401
- O.M. gosh, you guys!

12:49.468 --> 12:51.370
{\an3}Look at this dress
I found at the mall.

12:51.437 --> 12:53.139
[all gasp]

12:53.205 --> 12:55.941
{\an3}Ooh, when did we put a mirror
in the living room?

12:56.008 --> 12:57.843
{\an1}- That's not a mirror.
That's me!

12:57.910 --> 13:00.212
Now go take your dress back.
- What? No!

13:00.279 --> 13:01.413
You take yours back!

13:01.480 --> 13:02.681
[both growling]

13:02.748 --> 13:05.784
[all whistling]

13:05.851 --> 13:08.053
- That's it?
You got to be kidding me.

13:08.120 --> 13:10.156
Clyde and I wore the same shirt
on picture day,

13:10.222 --> 13:12.024
and we didn't care.

13:13.859 --> 13:16.662
{\an9}- It's a sister thing.
You wouldn't understand.

13:16.729 --> 13:18.430
- Well, let's go help them
work it out

13:18.497 --> 13:20.432
so we can have our house back.

13:20.499 --> 13:21.867
Oof!
- Negative.

13:21.934 --> 13:24.403
In this family, we have
a sister fight protocol:

13:24.470 --> 13:26.772
butt out and let them
resolve it on their own.

13:26.839 --> 13:28.908
- Yeah, well,
I have a protocol too,

13:28.974 --> 13:32.711
which is I don't like
pooping in a bucket.

13:35.514 --> 13:37.116
[sighs] Hey, guys.

13:37.183 --> 13:39.852
Now look, I know you've been
having a little problem--

13:39.919 --> 13:41.954
- Lincoln--
- But I think I can settle this.

13:42.021 --> 13:43.956
- Lincoln--
- Leni, why don't you

13:44.023 --> 13:45.891
just return the dress?
Lori once said

13:45.958 --> 13:48.127
blue makes you look
washed-out anyway.

13:48.194 --> 13:49.695
- Wait, what?
- Okay, okay.

13:49.762 --> 13:51.063
I'm just spitballing here.

13:51.130 --> 13:52.932
Lori, why don't you
return the dress?

13:52.998 --> 13:55.301
Leni says taffeta makes you look
like Aunt Ruth,

13:55.367 --> 13:57.036
and who wants that,
am I right?

13:57.102 --> 13:58.938
- [gasps] Excuse me?

13:59.004 --> 14:01.106
- So what do you say?
Ready to hug it out?

14:01.173 --> 14:03.676
- We already hugged it out.
We were fine.

14:03.742 --> 14:05.311
But now that I know that she

14:05.377 --> 14:09.215
thinks I look like Aunt Ruth,
we are definitely not fine.

14:09.281 --> 14:10.816
- You insulted my skin tone.

14:10.883 --> 14:12.751
Nothing's gonna make that right.

14:12.818 --> 14:14.320
You knew I can't tan!
- You literally betrayed me!

14:14.386 --> 14:15.521
- How could you say that?

14:15.588 --> 14:18.490
[both screaming at once]

14:18.557 --> 14:19.959
[muffled screaming]

14:20.025 --> 14:20.960
{\an3}- Ah!

14:21.026 --> 14:22.494
- Oh, nice job, Lincoln.

14:22.561 --> 14:24.530
We told you to stay out of it.

14:24.597 --> 14:27.099
{\an3}- I look good in every color!
- You're ruining my whole life!

14:27.166 --> 14:28.901
{\an7}- Based on rising
decibel levels,

14:28.968 --> 14:30.836
{\an7}I'm upping the threat level
in the house

14:30.903 --> 14:34.306
{\an7}from Thunderstorm
to Hissing Cat.

14:34.373 --> 14:36.242
Sisters, to your stations.

14:36.308 --> 14:39.912
- Uh, what's going on?
- Let us handle it.

14:41.247 --> 14:42.381
{\an8}- Ah!
- Scram, dude.

14:42.448 --> 14:44.817
{\an8}We need your room.
- What? Why?

14:44.883 --> 14:46.418
{\an8}- Lori's approaching the sector,

14:46.485 --> 14:48.554
{\an9}and we can't risk
a run-in with Leni.

14:48.621 --> 14:51.023
<i>[militaristic music]</i>

14:51.090 --> 14:53.125
- Coast is clear, brah.

14:53.192 --> 14:56.295
- Copy that. You may proceed.

14:56.362 --> 15:01.000
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:01.066 --> 15:04.003
[beeping]

15:04.069 --> 15:05.904
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:05.971 --> 15:09.241
<i>- Abort. Abort.</i>
<i>Leni's headed back up.</i>

15:09.308 --> 15:10.476
- Ah!

15:10.542 --> 15:11.677
- Ah!
- Lincoln!

15:11.744 --> 15:13.379
Make like a drum and beat it.

15:13.445 --> 15:17.182
[laughing] Get it?
But seriously, out.

15:17.249 --> 15:19.184
- Ah!

15:21.954 --> 15:23.355
[sighs]

15:23.422 --> 15:25.724
{\an3}- And then Mort realized he was
drinking regular,

15:25.791 --> 15:28.527
{\an3}not decaf!
[laughing]

15:28.594 --> 15:30.396
- Dinner was delicious, Mom.

15:30.462 --> 15:32.798
- Thanks, sweetie.

15:32.865 --> 15:35.868
- Yeah, thanks, Mom.
I am stuffed.

15:35.934 --> 15:38.237
{\an3}- Well, I hope you saved
room for dinner.

15:38.304 --> 15:41.073
- Wait, what?

15:41.140 --> 15:43.842
- Sister fight protocol:
Lori and Leni dine separately.

15:43.909 --> 15:45.311
{\an3}- And we have to eat
with them both,

15:45.377 --> 15:47.813
so they don't think
we're taking sides.

15:47.880 --> 15:51.550
- And then Mort realized
he was drinking regular,

15:51.617 --> 15:54.019
not decaf!
[laughing]

15:54.086 --> 15:56.021
- [laughing]

16:00.793 --> 16:02.494
- [whistling]
- Hey, what gives?

16:02.561 --> 16:04.396
{\an3}What happened to my sheets
and blanket?

16:04.463 --> 16:06.098
{\an1}- Sister fight protocol:
we used them

16:06.165 --> 16:07.933
{\an1}to make a divider in Lori
and Leni's room.

16:08.000 --> 16:11.904
{\an3}- Well, what am I supposed
to sleep under?

16:12.805 --> 16:14.873
- Try this.
- Ah!

16:14.940 --> 16:16.175
- [laughing]

16:16.241 --> 16:17.710
- All right, that's it!

16:17.776 --> 16:19.611
- Lincoln, what are you doing?

16:19.678 --> 16:21.547
Guys, we have a situation.

16:21.613 --> 16:24.383
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

16:24.450 --> 16:25.584
[both gasp]

16:25.651 --> 16:26.685
- I'm done with this!

16:26.752 --> 16:27.753
You guys and your stupid fight

16:27.820 --> 16:29.054
have ruined the whole day.

16:29.121 --> 16:31.390
It's time to get over it
and make up.

16:31.457 --> 16:32.991
{\an8}- Lincoln, this has
to run its course.

16:33.058 --> 16:36.161
{\an8}Sister fight protocol.
- Forget sister fight protocol!

16:36.228 --> 16:38.530
- Well, I'm not sleeping
in here with her.

16:38.597 --> 16:40.566
- I'm not sleeping
in here with her either.

16:40.632 --> 16:43.135
{\an3}- Fine--Luna, you sleep
in here tonight.

16:43.202 --> 16:44.370
Leni sleeps in your room.

16:44.436 --> 16:46.438
- Works for me.
- Me too.

16:46.505 --> 16:49.441
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:49.508 --> 16:51.577
- You're playing with fire, bro.

16:51.643 --> 16:53.779
[all agreeing]

16:53.846 --> 16:56.482
- Listen, by tomorrow, Lori and
Leni will have cooled off,

16:56.548 --> 16:58.984
and you'll be thanking me.

16:59.051 --> 16:59.985
[whistling]

17:00.052 --> 17:03.222
- [babbling]

17:03.288 --> 17:06.325
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:06.392 --> 17:07.693
{\an8}- [yawns]

17:07.760 --> 17:09.194
{\an8}Hmm. Peaceful.

17:09.261 --> 17:11.195
{\an8}Sounds like good ol' Lincoln
saved the day.

17:11.262 --> 17:14.199
{\an9}- Just admit you're wrong!
- You're wrong, dude!

17:14.266 --> 17:15.934
{\an8}- Or not.
[sighs]

17:16.001 --> 17:19.905
{\an8}Wait a minute, that didn't sound
like Lori and Leni.

17:19.972 --> 17:21.707
- Lori had the dress first.

17:21.773 --> 17:23.575
{\an1}She told me the whole story
last night.

17:23.642 --> 17:24.877
- Well, Leni told me her side,

17:24.943 --> 17:26.712
{\an3}and she clearly had
the dress first.

17:26.779 --> 17:29.748
{\an7}- Ha! That's funnier than most
of your lame jokes.

17:29.815 --> 17:31.483
{\an9}- Oh, I'm sorry,
I couldn't hear you.

17:31.550 --> 17:34.987
{\an8}I've gone partially deaf from
your horrible guitar playing.

17:35.053 --> 17:36.922
{\an8}- Guys, guys.
[both growling]

17:36.989 --> 17:40.993
{\an7}- Sister fight protocol:
divide and isolate.

17:42.761 --> 17:46.598
- You're paying for
new shocks, Lincoln.

17:49.468 --> 17:53.071
- This room is now off-limits.

17:53.138 --> 17:55.874
- Come on--
why is it always my room?

17:55.941 --> 17:57.810
{\an7}- Congratulations,
elder brother.

17:57.876 --> 17:59.545
{\an8}Thanks to you, the threat level

17:59.611 --> 18:01.613
{\an8}is now at Stampeding T-Rex.

18:01.680 --> 18:04.383
{\an8}- Stampeding T-Rex?
No!

18:04.450 --> 18:05.717
{\an8}We'll ride the storm out
in here.

18:05.784 --> 18:08.353
{\an8}- Did you remember the bucket?
- Dang it.

18:08.420 --> 18:10.189
{\an8}- Commencing T-Rex protocol.

18:10.255 --> 18:14.226
{\an8}I've got Big L
and we're on the move.

18:14.293 --> 18:16.929
- Roger that.

18:17.996 --> 18:19.765
- We're headed for the red zone.

18:19.832 --> 18:22.201
- Copy that.
We're headed for the green zone.

18:24.102 --> 18:25.471
[all growling]

18:25.537 --> 18:26.672
- Lola, what are you doing?

18:26.738 --> 18:28.006
This is the red zone!

18:28.073 --> 18:30.175
The door is red!
- Uh, hello?

18:30.242 --> 18:32.177
The carpet is green!

18:32.244 --> 18:35.180
[all shouting at once]

18:38.450 --> 18:41.386
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

18:41.453 --> 18:42.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:42.821 --> 18:44.690
- Here you go, Mrs. Loud.
- Thanks, Bobby.

18:44.756 --> 18:46.091
Just the large pepperoni for us.

18:46.158 --> 18:48.126
You can deliver the rest
to the front door.

18:48.193 --> 18:49.661
- Do I have to?
Lori told me

18:49.728 --> 18:52.030
the threat level is at
Stampeding T-Rex.

18:52.097 --> 18:54.766
- Just ring the doorbell
and run!

18:54.833 --> 18:56.535
- Ooh, good call, Mr. L.

18:56.602 --> 19:00.305
- Okay, first seating will be
Leni, Luan, and Lana.

19:00.372 --> 19:02.574
<i>- Roger. Copy that.</i>

19:02.641 --> 19:04.309
{\an1}- Gasp.
What are you doing?

19:04.376 --> 19:07.579
{\an1}You're supposed to be watching
Lori, Luna, and Lola.

19:07.646 --> 19:08.914
- Can't I have a break?

19:08.981 --> 19:10.749
I've been working
for nine hours.

19:10.816 --> 19:13.485
{\an1}- So have I, and you don't
see me complaining.

19:13.552 --> 19:16.522
{\an3}- Oh, yeah, 'cause you're always
such a ray of sunshine.

19:16.588 --> 19:19.858
{\an1}- At least I don't smell like
crusty athletic socks.

19:19.925 --> 19:22.628
{\an3}- Please, like Eau De Death
is better!

19:22.694 --> 19:24.930
{\an8}- Oh, boy. Here we go.
[both shouting]

19:24.997 --> 19:27.933
{\an7}We are now at
Erupting Volcano, people!

19:28.000 --> 19:30.569
{\an8}- Enough with your dumb chart!

19:30.636 --> 19:32.938
{\an7}- How would you like
to eat that hat?

19:33.005 --> 19:36.508
[all shouting at once]

19:36.575 --> 19:37.576
[grunting and shouting]

19:37.643 --> 19:39.278
- Hey, guys.

19:39.344 --> 19:42.414
[grunting and smacking]

19:42.481 --> 19:44.950
Clyde, come in.
- Hey, Lincoln. What's up?

19:45.017 --> 19:46.618
- Is your trundle bed available?

19:46.685 --> 19:48.921
{\an3}- Is it for you...
or Lori?

19:48.987 --> 19:51.356
{\an1}- For me, Clyde! Duh!
Sorry buddy.

19:51.423 --> 19:52.558
I'm a little stressed.

19:52.624 --> 19:54.426
{\an1}We're at Erupting Volcano
over here.

19:54.493 --> 19:55.994
- Say no more.

19:56.061 --> 19:58.030
- And the next thing I know,
they're all fighting!

19:58.096 --> 20:00.933
{\an3}- Interesting, and how did that
make you feel?

20:00.999 --> 20:02.801
- Clyde, what are you doing?

20:02.868 --> 20:04.803
{\an3}- When I take my problems
to Dr. Lopez,

20:04.870 --> 20:06.204
this is how she helps me.

20:06.271 --> 20:09.207
{\an1}- Okay, okay.
Anyway, I feel frustrated.

20:09.274 --> 20:11.510
{\an1}Their ridiculous
sister fight protocol

20:11.577 --> 20:12.844
only makes things worse.

20:12.911 --> 20:14.546
If they'd just let me help them,

20:14.613 --> 20:16.081
I could fix everything.

20:16.148 --> 20:18.784
{\an3}- I see.
So what do you plan to do?

20:18.850 --> 20:20.652
{\an1}- I'm gonna march back
in there tomorrow

20:20.719 --> 20:22.888
{\an1}and talk some sense
into those girls.

20:22.955 --> 20:24.556
- That seems sensible.
[watch beeping]

20:24.623 --> 20:26.725
Hmm, I see our time is up.

20:26.792 --> 20:28.293
- What? Can't I stay over?

20:28.360 --> 20:29.661
- Oh. I'm sorry.

20:29.728 --> 20:32.864
{\an3}I'm so used to hearing
Dr. Lopez say that.

20:32.931 --> 20:35.634
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

20:35.701 --> 20:38.503
- Okay. Here goes.

20:38.570 --> 20:40.372
Attention, Loud sisters!

20:40.439 --> 20:43.041
I am here to resolve
your conflicts.

20:43.108 --> 20:46.545
Please remain calm.
I am coming in.

20:46.612 --> 20:52.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:52.451 --> 20:55.120
<i>[pleasant music]</i>

20:55.187 --> 20:57.990
{\an3}What's going on?
What happened to the fighting?

20:58.056 --> 20:59.925
- Pfft, we're over that.
We made up.

20:59.992 --> 21:01.360
{\an8}- All of you?
- Correct.

21:01.426 --> 21:04.463
{\an8}Threat level is back
to Field of Daisies.

21:04.529 --> 21:07.065
{\an8}- Oh, thank goodness!
- I don't understand.

21:07.132 --> 21:08.867
{\an8}How did you fix everything?

21:08.934 --> 21:11.837
{\an7}- No, Lincoln.
You fixed everything.

21:11.903 --> 21:14.840
{\an8}- Me? How?
- By leaving.

21:14.906 --> 21:16.575
{\an1}- We told you,
if you just butted out,

21:16.642 --> 21:19.344
we'd resolve it on our own.
- But the dress--

21:19.411 --> 21:21.013
- I came up
with the perfect solution.

21:21.079 --> 21:23.448
Lori gets to wear it
on the days that end in Y,

21:23.515 --> 21:26.084
and I get to wear it
the rest of the time.

21:28.153 --> 21:30.989
{\an8}- And once they made up,
the rest of us made up.

21:31.056 --> 21:33.025
{\an7}- Huh, well, I guess
I've learned my lesson:

21:33.091 --> 21:35.861
{\an7}always respect
the sister fight protocol.

21:35.927 --> 21:37.696
{\an9}- Glad you're finally
getting it.

21:37.763 --> 21:39.665
{\an7}- Oh, I totally do,
believe me.

21:39.731 --> 21:40.999
{\an8}Next time Lynn says she needs

21:41.066 --> 21:42.968
{\an7}a windshield wiper
when Lisa talks,

21:43.035 --> 21:45.470
{\an7}or Lana says Lola snores
like Pop Pop,

21:45.537 --> 21:47.773
{\an8}I am staying out of it.

21:47.839 --> 21:51.243
{\an8}- You said what now, sporty?

21:51.309 --> 21:53.045
{\an8}- Oh, I snore, do I?

21:53.111 --> 21:55.947
{\an9}How can you hear me over all
your sleep-farting?

21:56.014 --> 21:58.483
- Whew, can't wait to use
the real toilet.

21:58.550 --> 22:00.085
[all shouting at once]

22:00.152 --> 22:03.121
Ah! Retreat! Retreat!
- Wait for me!

22:03.188 --> 22:04.423
[all shouting at once]

22:04.489 --> 22:05.991
[banging and crashing]

22:10.629 --> 22:12.097
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Cramped inside</i>
<i>this tiny space ♪</i>

22:12.164 --> 22:13.932
{\an8}<i>♪ May sound bad</i>
<i>but ain't the case ♪</i>

22:13.999 --> 22:16.868
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:16.935 --> 22:19.337
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Duck and dodge</i>
<i>and push and shove ♪</i>

22:19.404 --> 22:23.408
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way we show</i>
<i>our love in the Loud house ♪</i>

22:23.475 --> 22:24.776
{\an8}<i>- ♪ Loud house ♪</i>

22:24.843 --> 22:26.378
{\an8}<i>♪ Laundry piles</i>
<i>stacked up high ♪</i>

22:26.445 --> 22:27.546
{\an8}<i>♪ Hand-me-downs</i>
<i>that make me cry ♪</i>

22:27.612 --> 22:28.780
{\an8}<i>♪ Stand in line to take a pee ♪</i>

22:28.847 --> 22:30.215
{\an8}<i>♪ Never any privacy ♪</i>

22:30.282 --> 22:32.751
{\an8}<i>♪ Chaos with 11 kids ♪</i>

22:32.818 --> 22:35.253
{\an8}<i>♪ That's the way</i>
<i>it always is ♪</i>

22:35.320 --> 22:36.655
{\an8}<i>♪ In the Loud house ♪</i>
